Heatmap Using ggplot2 Package

Davit Sargsyan

08/12/2017

These are examples of creating heatmaps with ggplot2 package. For more examples on constructing heatmaps, see my answer on Stack Overflow my answer on Stack Overflow

# Load packages----
require(data.table)
require(ggplot2)
require(ggdendro)

set.seed(100)

# Data----
n.row <- 10
n.col <- 8
n.grp <- 2

dt1 <- data.table(rowVar = factor(paste("Row",
                                        rep(LETTERS[1:n.row],
                                            n.col))),
                  colVar = factor(paste("Column",
                                        rep(rev(LETTERS[1:n.col]),
                                            each = n.row))),
                  grpVar = factor(paste("Group",
                                        sample(1:2,
                                               n.row*n.col,
                                               replace = TRUE))),
                  valVar = rnorm(n.row*n.col))
head(dt1)
# Plot rectangular heatmap----
p1 <- ggplot(data = dt1) +
  geom_tile(aes(x =  colVar,
                y = rowVar,
                fill = valVar),
            color = "black") +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "red", 
                       high = "green", 
                       mid = "black", 
                       midpoint = 0, 
                       # limit = c(-10, 10), 
                       name = "Magnitude") +
  scale_x_discrete("Column Variable",
                   expand = c(0, 0)) + 
  scale_y_discrete("Row Variable",
                   expand = c(0, 0)) +
  ggtitle("Heatmap") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 20,
                                   hjust = 1),
        # legend.position = "top",
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
print(p1)

# Plot heatmap with grouping variable----
p2 <- ggplot(data = dt1) +
  facet_wrap(~ grpVar,
             scales = "free_y") +
  geom_tile(aes(x =  colVar,
                y = rowVar,
                fill = valVar),
            color = "black") +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "red", 
                       high = "green", 
                       mid = "black", 
                       midpoint = 0, 
                       # limit = c(-10, 10), 
                       name = "Magnitude") +
  scale_x_discrete("Column Variable",
                   expand = c(0, 0)) + 
  scale_y_discrete("Row Variable",
                   expand = c(0, 0)) +
  ggtitle("Heatmap") + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 20,
                                   hjust = 1),
        # legend.position = "top",
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
print(p2)

Plot correlation of columns:

dt2 <- dcast.data.table(data = dt1,
                        rowVar ~ colVar,
                        value.var = "valVar")
cor1 <- cor(dt2[, -1])
heatmap(cor1,
        col = rev(heat.colors(10)))

# Make dendrogram data----
dhc <- as.dendrogram(hclust(d = as.dist(cor1 + 1)),
                     horiz = TRUE)
ddata <- dendro_data(dhc, 
                     type = "rectangle")

# Segment data----
dtp1 <- segment(ddata)
# Hitmap data----
dtp2 <- melt.data.table(data.table(rowNames = rownames(cor1),
                                   cor1),
                        id.vars = 1,
                        measure.vars = 2:(ncol(cor1) + 1),
                        variable.name = "colNames")
dtp2$rowNames <- factor(dtp2$rowNames,
                        levels = ddata$labels$label)
dtp2$colNames <- factor(dtp2$colNames,
                        levels = ddata$labels$label)
p1 <- ggplot(data = dtp2) +
  # Y-axis dendrogram
  geom_segment(data = dtp1,
               aes(x = 2*y + 8,
                   y = x, 
                   xend = 2*yend + 8,
                   yend = xend),
               size = 1) +
  # X-axis dendrogram
  geom_segment(data = dtp1,
               aes(x = x,
                   y = 2*y + 8, 
                   xend = xend,
                   yend = 2*yend + 8),
               size = 1) +
  geom_tile(aes(x =  colNames,
                y = rowNames, 
                fill = value),
            color = "white") +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "red", 
                       high = "green", 
                       mid = "grey", 
                       midpoint = 0, 
                       name = "Correlation",
                       limits = c(-1, 1)) +
  scale_x_discrete("",
                   expand = c(0, 0)) +
  scale_y_discrete("",
                   expand = c(0, 0)) +
  ggtitle("") + 
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45,
                                   hjust = 1))
print(p1)

If the table is long and narrow, a more compact way to present the data is to make the table into a round shape, i.e. donut.

# Data----
n.row <- 100

dt2 <- data.frame(`ColumnA` = rnorm(n.row),
                  `ColumnB` = rnorm(n.row))
rownames(dt2) <- paste("Row",
                       1:n.row,
                       sep = "")
head(dt2)
# Compute distances between colNamess----
sampleDists <- dist(dt2)

# Example of the plot using library 'ape'----
plot(ape::as.phylo(x = hclust(sampleDists)),
     type = "fan")

# Make dendrogram data----
dhc <- as.dendrogram(hclust(d = sampleDists),
                     horiz = TRUE)
ddata <- dendro_data(dhc, 
                     type = "rectangle")

# Segment data----
dtp1 <- segment(ddata)

# Hitmap data----
dtp2 <- melt.data.table(data.table(rowNames = rownames(dt2),
                                   dt2),
                        id.vars = 1,
                        measure.vars = 2:3,
                        variable.name = "colNames")
dtp2$rowNames <- factor(dtp2$rowNames,
                        levels = ddata$labels$label)


p1 <- ggplot(data = dtp2) +
  coord_polar("y",
              start = 0,
              direction = -1) +
  geom_tile(aes(x =  as.numeric(colNames),
                y = rowNames, 
                fill = value),
            color = "white") +
  geom_text(data = dtp2[colNames == "ColumnA", ],
            aes(x = rep(1.75,
                        nlevels(rowNames)),
                y = rowNames,
                angle = 90 + seq(from = 0,
                                 to = 360,
                                 length.out = nlevels(rowNames))[as.numeric(rowNames)],
                label = unique(rowNames)),
            hjust = 0) +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "red", 
                       high = "green", 
                       mid = "grey", 
                       midpoint = 0, 
                       name = "Legend") +
  scale_y_discrete("",
                   expand = c(0, 0)) +
  ggtitle("Donut Hitmap with Dendrogram") + 
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank()) +
  geom_segment(data = dtp1,
               aes(x = -sqrt(y) + 1.5,
                   y = x, 
                   xend = -sqrt(yend) + 1.5,
                   yend = xend),
               size = 1) 
print(p1)
